data.value: A firewall system is a form of network security put in place to monitor traffic flow, both being received and sent through the network. A firewall will abide by a specific rule set to the network in which it is being implemented. It effectively constructs a barrier between networks; preventing any unauthorized access. With these features, it may be confusing as to whether a firewall is either software or a hardware appliance. The answer to that is simple; it can be both! Despite this, the most common Firewall configuration will consist of both.
